    "layoutDecisions": "The layout is structured vertically to mirror the provided reference image and prioritize a clear, scannable list of settings.  The `appbar` and bottom navigation components are placed at the top and bottom respectively, adhering to the screen-level auto-layout guidelines.  This ensures these elements are always visible and accessible.  A content-holder auto-layout is used to contain the scrollable list of settings, with 16px spacing between each item to provide visual separation without excessive whitespace.",
